Product description

Color:Black

Vesatile Application for Work and Entertainment
Present the content from your computer to larger display in mirror mode, so everybody follows you while doing a speech, a presentation, a meeting etc;
Multi-tasking with extend mode when connecting with external display, you can double your workspace or enjoy a movie when doing some easy task;
Sharp Image with 4K Resolution
The Mini DisplayPort Adapter can support the resolution of up to 3840x2160@30Hz refresh rate. Brighter and sharper images make you immersed in a more colorful and vivid world. It is ideal for home theater.
Specification
Input: Mini DisplayPort
Output: HDMI
Transmit audio and video from the mini DisplayPort to HDMI.
Supports video resolutions up to 3840x2160
Supports uncompressed audio such as LPCM
Cable Length: 0.6ft
Compatibility(Partial List)
MacBook Air 2015, 2016; MacBook Pro 2011,2012, 2013,2014, 2015; iMac
Surface Pro 3, Surface Pro 4, Surface Pro 5(NOT Surface/Surface 2 for Windows RT)
ThinkPad P71, ThinkPad P51 Mobile Workstation, ThinkPad X1 Yoga, ThinkPad X1 Carbon (4th Gen), ThinkPad T470s, ThinkPad T470p, ThinkPad T570, ThinkPad Yoga 370, ThinkPad L470, ThinkPad L470
Dell XPS Tower Special Edition (2016), Dell New XPS Tower
Notes
- Mini DisplayPort that supports both audio and video is only available on Apple devices released after April 2010. Please make sure whether your device is compatible with the adapter before purchasing it.It is not compatible with MacBook Pro released after 2016.
- It can only transmit from mini DisplayPort to HDMI because it is not bidirectional.
- Please use HDMI version 1.4 cable within 8 meters to ensure the high performance of this item.
- It is not compatible Thunderbolt 3.0
Package
Mini DisplayPort to HDMI adapter x1

      Melissa
      5.0 out of 5 stars transferred streaming video from iMac to smartTV. (With some adjustments to iMac settings)
      Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2019
      Color: BlackVerified Purchase
      My smartTV doesn't have the hulu app on it, and I got tired of watching hulu on my iMac (late 2015 model). After some reading, I discovered that I needed to connect the iMac and the TV with a HDMI cable. However, the iMac didn't have a HDMI port on the back. It had only USB ports and two thunderbolt 2 ports. So I bought this device to connect the HDMI cable to my computer via the thunderbolt 2 port.

      The device worked fine, once I made a few tweaks. First, on my smartTV, I pressed the "input" button on the remote control. The input was already set to HDMI-2; this is the port (on the side of the TV) where the comcast/xfinity box connected. So, the HDMI port on the back of my TV turned out to be HDMI-1.

      I selected HDMI-1, and I saw my computer wallpaper, but my HULU safari window was missing on my TV display even though it showed up on my iMAC display. To fix this, I had to go to Apple Preferences / Displays. Go to the "Arrangement" tab and place a check in the "Mirror Displays' checkbox. This means that the TV screen will be a matching copy of the iMac screen. After closing the Apple "Preferences" window, I launched hulu, and I expanded the video to full-screen mode. My TV showed an identical image.

      But...at first, the audio continued to come from my iMac speakers instead of the TV. (The TV has much higher-quality speakers than the iMac, so I needed to adjust this. Back in the Apple Preferences area, I accessed "Sound". Now, with the cable connected, a new option appeared in the list of devices: Name: #320i-B2; Type: HDMI. "Internal Speakers" was still highlighted by default, so I clicked on the new HDMI option to select it.

      Then everything worked fine. (Of course the color wasn't as nice on my TV as on the iMac. I'm still working on troubleshooting that.) Fortunately, when I went to watch hulu again the next day, my iMac had remembered the tweaks I described above, so I didn't have to repeat all the steps. I simply had to change the TV's input from HDMI-2 to HDMI-1.

      Ho acquistato questo adattatore per collegare il mio mac ad un monitor esterno. Il prodotto corrisponde alla descrizione.       5.0 out of 5 stars Adattatore affidabile e di ottima qualità
      Reviewed in Italy on January 13, 2018
      Ho acquistato questo adattatore per collegare il mio mac ad un monitor esterno. Il prodotto corrisponde alla descrizione. Appena ho aperto la confezione mi è sembrato sei aver avuto davanti un prodotto di qualità, impressione che ho verificato nel mio mese di utilizzo. La mini displayport è placcata in oro e nei numerosi collegamenti che ho effettuato non si è minimamente rovinata. Stessa considerazione vale per l’ingresso femmina dell'HDMI. Anche il cavo è molto robusto, nonostante gli stressanti piegamenti che ha subito in questo mese non si sono formate piegature e cosa più importante le due estremità sono ancora attaccate saldamente alle parti in plastica dell’HDMI e della mini displayport. Io lo utilizzo sempre per una connessione 1080p a 60 Hz e devo dire che non ho mai avuto nessun genere di problema sia sotto l’aspetto video che quello audio. E’ un prodotto dal design semplice che svolge egregiamente il suo lavoro trasmettendo con fedeltà i video e gli audio al mio monitor. Forse 11 euro sono un po’ tanti ma al momento dell’acquisto ho anche considerato il fatto che supporta la risoluzione 4K a 30 Hz caratteristica che spero di poter sfruttare in qualche occasione in futuro. Prodotto di ottima qualità affidabile e con un buon prezzo ne consiglio l’acquisto.
